  "description": [
    "In This Issue Whats behind the move to put Unions under antitrust laws Why do they want to weaken Labor A noted at torney gives some answers in Page 4 Think It Over Whats new at the Toledo Health Retiree Center For Your Union and Mine By RICHARD T GOSSER Vice President UAW OUR UNITED LABOR COMMITTEE has reported that 2 since the last election 35000 persons have been dropped from the voters registration rolls in Lucas County In the past few weeks about 5000 of these persons have taken the time and trouble to fill in their registration notices and become eligible again But when you learn that in Lucas County there are only 181000 persons registered out of a total of 250000 to 260000 you can see we have a long way to go Our registration in this community has been steadily drop 9 ping since 1960 In that year when we voted for a President Congressmen state legislators and county officials we hit a record of over 220000 registrations That was even better than two years earlier when we had the miscalled RighttoWork amend ment facing us in Ohio and 216000 persons in this county were registered"
  ],
